Up ahead they heard a sudden burst of machine gun fire, and then silence.
"uh oh" said Billy. "Maybe this isnt such a good idea"
But it was too late, because they could already see the poor newly armed pony had been gunned down by an angry army patrol. Nearby was another heap of bodies.
Maybe this wasnt a good idea at all thought the unicorn. Maybe they had made a terrible mistake.
The guards approached Billy and the unicorn, and raised their guns shouting "HALT"
Oh no! what could they do? They were just an aging scottish comedian and a magical unicorn! They couldn't handle that sort of firepower!
"Wait a minute!" Thought the unicorn. "Thats right. I'm magic!"
With a toss of his head he did his thing, and suddenly all of the nasty guns were turned into spiralisers!
He knew they were safe now. Afterall spiralisers arent useful for anything, apart from cutting the hands of people trying to use them!
The soldiers knew that too, and so they had no choice but to let the unicorn and comedian pass.
They cantered along, and soon came to a single building. There was a big red door on it, so with nothing else to do, they pushed on inside.
There they found the strangest sight. There seemed to be some sort of wolf man making a cake?!?

The wolf man turned to the confused pair. "Oh hello. Welcome to my secret bakery. I hope the security didnt bother you too much - I have to have lots of armed guards to make sure I dont get mistaken for a nasty werewolf"
Billy accepted this news stoically. "Its nae bother young lad. Tell us, whats yer name?"
The wolfman replied, "Oh its magical Trevor. You know the tricks I do are ever so clever. Can I help you with something?"
The unicorn knew this was his big chance. If this magical cake making wolfman couldn't help him, no one could. He tentatively stepped forward and leant in close so Trevor could hear him,

"I really want to go to the woooorld of tomorrow!" he whispered. "I've been staying in this terrible grey world full of cute animals where everyone is dead, so I need to go somewhere else and make new friends"
Trevor nodded sagely. "No problem, I can do that for you. But what of you Mr Connolly, how can I help you?"
Billy thought for a moment. "Well I've come this far, I might as well continue on tha journey!"
Trevor accepted this statement and calmly closed his eyes. "Very well, here, you both need to eat one of these". He held out two cupcakes in his razor sharp claws.

Both the unicorn and Billy suddenly realised they hadn't eaten for a long time, and crossing a desert was hungry work! They crammed the cupcakes into their gaping maws, barely chewing before swallowing the bounty offered to them.
They both felt very sleepy, and so lay down to have a nice nap.
The unicorn's eyes suddenly flicked open.
He looked down at his hands
What on earth was going on?
At this point a passing hovercar slowed down, and kindly old Mr Plot Exposition jumped out to explain

"It seems you have been sent into the future, but something strange happened and you have merged with your travelling companion. It looks like you have become an old scientist, rather than a unicorn!"
....and that children, is the story of how the whispering unicorn made its way into the future.
